items.no: - Go back and look at what you did after session 1 in the Identifying Values exercise. Consider the connection between these personal values and the values upon which your startup company might be based. - Look for ways in which the external work you would be doing in the world is like a metaphor for the internal qualities that you are in the process of learning to embody. Finding this alignment can be a recipe for very deep meaning that connects the personal to the outer world. - Use clarifying distinctions to narrow down what gets your passion flowing. Does it need to be something that directly solves a specific problem in the world, or would you be content to work on something more obscure, empowering others to solve problems with what you provide? Would you be satisfied with creating a product whose main contribution to the world is to save people time by making things more efficient? Or would it need to make a more qualitative impact on the world for you to feel excited about it? You can continue to come up with more distinctions like this and see where it takes you.
